input: Write a song of nature's beauty.
output:
(Verse 1)
O, fairest forest, with leaves of green,
How thou dost dance in summer's gentle sheen!
Thy trees, like sentinels of earth and sky,
Do stand as guardians o'er the verdant eye.

(Chorus)
Ah, nature's beauty, thou art divine,
A wonder to behold, a sight sublime.
In thine own splendor, thou dost shine so bright,
A treasure trove of life, in all thy light.

(Verse 2)
The rivers flow, like silken streams,
Through vales of green, where sunbeams gleam.
The mountains rise, in grandeur high,
And in their peaks, the winds do softly sigh.

(Chorus)
Ah, nature's beauty, thou art divine,
A wonder to behold, a sight sublime.
In thine own splendor, thou dost shine so bright,
A treasure trove of life, in all thy light.

(Bridge)
The creatures roam, with gentle ease,
Through fields and woods, where wildflowers breathe.
The sky above, a canvas wide,
Doth paint the colors, of the morning's pride.

(Chorus)
Ah, nature's beauty, thou art divine,
A wonder to behold, a sight sublime.
In thine own splendor, thou dost shine so bright,
A treasure trove of life, in all thy light.
